			<description><![CDATA[<p>
SheSpeaks is an influencer marketing platform. We are a fast-paced, creative and entrepreneurial organization working with an exciting line up of new and leading brands including American Express, P&amp;G, L&#39;Oreal and occasionally some great star talent too! We deliver compelling marketing programs for our clients which include sampling new products to some of our 200,000 community members, activating influential bloggers, twitter events, social media networking, research studies and in-person events.</p>
<p>
Marketing Assistant will focus on one or more of the following key business areas:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Community management and social media support.</li>
<li>
Member communications</li>
<li>
Member acquisition</li>
<li>
Member experience</li>
<li>
Strategic partnerships</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Key responsibilities include:&nbsp; </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Assist with influencers &amp; Blogger Society growth and management</li>
<li>
Development and execution of member communications</li>
<li>
Competitor research and identification of industry best practices</li>
<li>
Collation &amp; Analysis of existing program results.</li>
<li>
Support the Program Team to execute client programs &amp; client communications</li>
<li>
Participate in internal team meetings</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<p>
The Marketing Assistant must be a self-starter; possess an entrepreneurial spirit needed to work within a fast-paced, start-up environment; demonstrate maturity, poise and good humor; and have the ability to work well independently and within a team.</p>
<p>
Additional qualifications include: Work experience or coursework focus in marketing, social media strategy or related field</p>
<ul>
<li>
Demonstrated consumer-facing writing ability&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Demonstrated ability to juggle multiple priorities at once</li>
<li>
Exceptional oral and written communication skills</li>
<li>
Knowledge in social media and social engagement tactics&nbsp;</li>
<li>
Flexibility to work on a variety of projects</li>
<li>
Proficient in Microsoft Office Suite, including Excel, PowerPoint and Word</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Compensation:</strong> Course credit, if available, or a modest stipend for travel</p>
<p>
<strong>Benefits of working at SheSpeaks include:</strong></p>
<p>
A fun and dynamic team working environment, centrally located offices in New York City.&nbsp; Experience in working with new and exciting brand products from Fortune 500 brand teams and their agencies.&nbsp; The opportunity to work across of variety of categories including consumer packaged goods, beauty, food, personal care, TV media etc.&nbsp; The opportunity to be empowered to bring your ideas to life for the SheSpeaks brand and clients.&nbsp; Thursday team lunch and other fun team activities!</p>
